  "familyNotes": "QK-norm architecture (Qwen3 family, 28 layers). HAND-AUTHORED per-layer extension built from the ffn_down \u00d7 use_more_bits-set drill on 2026-04-28: 28 ffn_down tensors \u00d7 {Q2_K, Q4_K, IQ4_XS, Q6_K} measurements. Two empirical findings drove this profile: (1) per-layer Q2_K sum (~1.18 PPL) \u2248 category-level Q4_K (linear regime) but is ~3000\u00d7 lower than category-level Q2_K (+3709 PPL) \u2014 at catastrophic-bpw, single-tensor ablations under-predict compounding effects. (2) Stock's use_more_bits set is empirically miscalibrated on this model: protected layers' mean Q4_K \u0394 is +0.001, unprotected is +0.012 (9\u00d7 ratio inverted). Recommended workflow: pair this profile with ApplyStockBaseline=false and target Q4_K_M (4.95 bpw) \u2014 the resulting recipe demotes all 14 use_more_bits-protected ffn_down layers from Q6_K to Q4_K, predicted quality cost dominated by blk.11 (\u0394 \u2248 +0.025).",
